==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Edify
<hw>Ed"i*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Edified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Edifying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧difier</ets>,
L. <ets>aedificare</ets>; <ets>aedes</ets> a building, house, orig., a
fireplace (akin to Gr. <?/ to burn, Skr. <ets>idh</ets> to kindle, OHG.
<ets>eit</ets> funeral pile, AS. <ets>⟦amac⟧d</ets>, OIr. <ets>aed</ets>
fire) + <ets>facere</ets> to make. See <er>Fact</er>,
<er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To build; to construct.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There was a holy chapel <qex>edified</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To instruct and improve, especially in moral and
religious knowledge; to teach.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It does not appear probable that our dispute [about miracles]
would either <qex>edify</qex> or enlighten the public.</q>
<rj><qau>Gibbon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To teach or persuade.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Edify</ent>⟦br⟧

